    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Therefore he said unto Judah,.... To the nobles and principal men of the kingdom: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "let us build these cities; which he, no doubt, particularly mentioned by name, and pointed at; that is, repair and fortify them, and put them into a better condition of defence: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and make about them walls and towers, gates and bars; which are always made to fortified places, to protect the inhabitants, and keep out an enemy: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "while the land is yet before us; in our power, no enemy in it, nor any to hinder or molest: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because we have sought the Lord our God, we have sought him, and he hath given us rest on every side; had set up his pure worship, reformed abuses in it, and removed idolatry from it, and closely attended to the service of the sanctuary, which was well pleasing to God; the happy effect of which they experienced, rest from all their enemies round about them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "so that they built, and prospered; they began, and went on, and finished, there being nothing to hinder them. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "so that they built, and prospered; they began, and went on, and finished, there being nothing to hinder them. ",
