    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Asa had also a well-equipped, well-armed army. The men of Judah were armed with a large shield and lance (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 12:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), the Benjamites with a small shield and bow (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 8:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The numbers are great; of Judah 300,000, of Benjamin 280,000 men. Since in these numbers the whole population capable of bearing arms is included, 300,000 men does not appear too large for Judah, but 280,000 is a very large number for Benjamin, and is founded probably on an overestimate. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
